<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-10T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="1067" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1067">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/12–1145: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-11T10:00:00+07:00">December 11,
                                1945—10 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received December 11—3:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2137. [To Consul General at Tientsin:] Please advise if situation described
                        your unnumbered December 7, 4 p.m.<note n="59" xml:id="d1067fn59">See
                            telegram No. 26, <ref target="#pg_1416">p. 1416</ref>.</note> has been
                        corrected as result of our protest to Foreign Office reported Embassy’s
                        telegram 2014 [<hi rend="italic">2114</hi>], December 7. (Sent to Tientsin,
                        repeated to Department.) Foreign Office is being informed [of] continued
                        violation of agreement with Embassy but formal protest will be delayed
                        pending reply this telegram.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>